Audi to Sell 1.5 Million Cars by 2014, Automotive News Reports

-- B y   K a r i n   M a t u s s e k
-- 
2011-07-09T12:29:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-09/audi-to-sell-1-5-million-cars-by-2014-automotive-news-reports.html
Volkswagen AG (VOW) â€™s Audi unit plans to
sell 1.5 million cars by 2014, a year ahead of schedule,
 Automotive News Europe  reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
Rupert Stadler.  Stadler confirmed reports that the automaker plans to sell
2 million cars by 2020, the magazine said in an e-mailed preview
of an article. The target for this year is 1.2 million cars.
The lineup will increase to 50 models by 2050 from 42 in 2015
and 38 this year, Stadler said, according to Automotive News  The carmaker may also build an engine and transmission
plant in  North America , which could be shared with the VW brand,
the magazine said, citing an unidentified person at Audi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
